Western Cape detectives are investigating the murders of six people killed in Khayelitsha. eNCA's Nobesuthu Hejana is covering this story. Courtesy of #DStv403  CAPE TOWN - Western Cape detectives are investigating the murders of six people killed in Khayelitsha on Sunday. Police say three unknown gunmen fired shots randomly at the victims in Lindela Road in the Enkanini informal settlement at around 4pm. READ:Â Six men shot and killed in Umlazi The victims are two women and four men, estimated to be between the ages of 22 and 27 years. Sunday's mass shooting come less than a week after five other people were killed in the same township.